# TanStack Start routes

- One route per file under `src/routes/`. Landing: `index.tsx` → `/`. App layout: `app.tsx` → `/app` with `<Outlet />`.
- App child routes use dot notation: `app.farmers.tsx` → `/app/farmers`, `app.index.tsx` → `/app/`.
- Dynamic segments use bare `$`: `users/$id.tsx`, not `{id}`.
- Do not create `src/pages/`, `_app/`, or Next.js-style layouts.
- Do not edit `src/routeTree.gen.ts` — it is auto-generated.
- Route `head()` for page titles/meta; fonts load in `__root.tsx`.

```tsx
// ✅ App child route pattern
import { createFileRoute } from "@tanstack/react-router";

export const Route = createFileRoute("/app/farmers")({
  component: FarmersPage,
});
```
